{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778431693118,"sessionID":"ses_1ed3d5e87ffe4PVbbsUuqSlRrO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_SiBp5Wjk2AP7belIpOHgZlJO","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_33658722.md","offset":1,"limit":200},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/references_cache/PMID_33658722.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: reference_id: PMID:33658722\n3: title: The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.\n4: authors:\n5: - Suzuki T\n6: journal: Nat Rev Mol Cell Biol\n7: year: '2021'\n8: doi: 10.1038/s41580-021-00342-0\n9: keywords:\n10: - Animals\n11: - Codon/genetics\n12: - Humans\n13: - Protein Biosynthesis/genetics\n14: - \"RNA Processing, Post-Transcriptional/genetics\"\n15: - \"RNA, Messenger/genetics, metabolism\"\n16: - \"RNA, Transfer/genetics\"\n17: content_type: abstract_only\n18: ---\n19: \n20: # The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.\n21: **Authors:** Suzuki T\n22: **Journal:** Nat Rev Mol Cell Biol (2021)\n23: **DOI:** [10.1038/s41580-021-00342-0](https://doi.org/10.1038/s41580-021-00342-0)\n24: \n25: ## Content\n26: \n27: 1. Nat Rev Mol Cell Biol. 2021 Jun;22(6):375-392. doi:\n28: 10.1038/s41580-021-00342-0.  Epub 2021 Mar 3.\n29: \n30: The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.\n31: \n32: Suzuki T(1).\n33: \n34: Author information:\n35: (1)Department of Chemistry and Biotechnology, Graduate School of Engineering, \n36: The University of Tokyo, Tokyo, Japan. ts@chembio.t.u-tokyo.ac.jp.\n37: \n38: Transfer RNA (tRNA) is an adapter molecule that links a specific codon in mRNA \n39: with its corresponding amino acid during protein synthesis. tRNAs are \n40: enzymatically modified post-transcriptionally. A wide variety of tRNA \n41: modifications are found in the tRNA anticodon, which are crucial for precise \n42: codon recognition and reading frame maintenance, thereby ensuring accurate and \n43: efficient protein synthesis. In addition, tRNA-body regions are also frequently \n44: modified and thus stabilized in the cell. Over the past two decades, 16 novel \n45: tRNA modifications were discovered in various organisms, and the chemical space \n46: of tRNA modification continues to expand. Recent studies have revealed that tRNA \n47: modifications can be dynamically altered in response to levels of cellular \n48: metabolites and environmental stresses. Importantly, we now understand that \n49: deficiencies in tRNA modification can have pathological consequences, which are \n50: termed 'RNA modopathies'. Dysregulation of tRNA modification is involved in \n51: mitochondrial diseases, neurological disorders and cancer.\n52: \n53: DOI: 10.1038/s41580-021-00342-0\n54: PMID: 33658722 [Indexed for MEDLINE]\n\n(End of file - total 54 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nreference_id: PMID:33658722\ntitle: The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.\nauthors:\n- Suzuki T\njournal: Nat Rev Mol Cell Biol\nyear: '2021'\ndoi: 10.1038/s41580-021-00342-0\nkeywords:\n- Animals\n- Codon/genetics\n- Humans\n- Protein Biosynthesis/genetics\n- \"RNA Processing, Post-Transcriptional/genetics\"\n- \"RNA, Messenger/genetics, metabolism\"\n- \"RNA, Transfer/genetics\"\ncontent_type: abstract_only\n---\n\n# The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"references_cache/PMID_33658722.md","time":{"start":1778431693111,"end":1778431693117}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bf3b8c8ea418792016a00b6cc92ac8190883fe22206402503"}},"id":"prt_e12ca0f4200148Vogr4MyjTjiA","sessionID":"ses_1ed3d5e87ffe4PVbbsUuqSlRrO","messageID":"msg_e12ca0b64001qtszNTAxargkv1"}}
