{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778432179429,"sessionID":"ses_1ed3d5e87ffe4PVbbsUuqSlRrO","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_z6pBfcUg0ABmzKL4meDJrf1K","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+# Research Notes for GO:0016430 Obsoletion Cleanup\n+\n+## PMID:33658722 \"The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.\"\n+\n+Validated bibliographic metadata using `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:33658722`.\n+\n+The PMID cited in the existing obsoletion comment resolves to a 2021 review on tRNA modifications by T. Suzuki in Nature Reviews Molecular Cell Biology. The cached PubMed abstract confirms that the publication is about tRNA modifications broadly; the current edit does not introduce or alter this reference, but preserves it in the existing obsoletion rationale.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:33658722 \"Transfer RNA (tRNA) is an adapter molecule that links a specific codon in mRNA with its corresponding amino acid during protein synthesis. tRNAs are enzymatically modified post-transcriptionally.\"\n+\n+## Annotation and External Usage Checks\n+\n+Attempted direct annotation and external ontology usage checks with OAK:\n+\n+* `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0016430`\n+* `runoak -i ubergraph: usages GO:0016430`\n+\n+Both commands failed in this environment before querying due to a local Python dependency error in OAK/LinkML: `AttributeError: type object 'Format' has no attribute 'JSON'`. Because this change only removes synonyms from an already-obsolete term and does not newly obsolete the term or change replacement guidance, no annotation migration was performed.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO:0016430 Obsoletion Cleanup\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+This task concerns cleanup of an already-obsolete molecular function term, `GO:0016430` obsolete tRNA (adenine-N6)-methyltransferase activity.\n+\n+## Applicable Guidance\n+\n+The term is in the catalytic activity branch and originally represented an enzyme reaction. Reaction-term guidance was consulted, but no reaction definition, RHEA mapping, EC mapping, or logical axiom was added or changed in this cleanup.\n+\n+The obsoletion pattern is the relevant pattern for the edit:\n+\n+* obsolete label is retained as `obsolete <original label>`\n+* namespace and historical obsolete definition are retained\n+* obsoletion comment and term tracker item are retained\n+* `is_obsolete: true` is retained\n+* synonyms are removed, consistent with GO obsoletion guidance that obsolete terms should not retain synonyms unless explicitly requested\n+\n+## Logical Axioms\n+\n+No `intersection_of`, `is_a`, or `relationship` tags were added. The obsolete stanza has no logical axioms after the cleanup.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA RESEARCH.md\nA DESIGN_PATTERNS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/RESEARCH.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@\n+# Research Notes for GO:0016430 Obsoletion Cleanup\n+\n+## PMID:33658722 \"The expanding world of tRNA modifications and their disease relevance.\"\n+\n+Validated bibliographic metadata using `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:33658722`.\n+\n+The PMID cited in the existing obsoletion comment resolves to a 2021 review on tRNA modifications by T. Suzuki in Nature Reviews Molecular Cell Biology. The cached PubMed abstract confirms that the publication is about tRNA modifications broadly; the current edit does not introduce or alter this reference, but preserves it in the existing obsoletion rationale.\n+\n+* SUPPORT: PMID:33658722 \"Transfer RNA (tRNA) is an adapter molecule that links a specific codon in mRNA with its corresponding amino acid during protein synthesis. tRNAs are enzymatically modified post-transcriptionally.\"\n+\n+## Annotation and External Usage Checks\n+\n+Attempted direct annotation and external ontology usage checks with OAK:\n+\n+* `runoak -i amigo: associations GO:0016430`\n+* `runoak -i ubergraph: usages GO:0016430`\n+\n+Both commands failed in this environment before querying due to a local Python dependency error in OAK/LinkML: `AttributeError: type object 'Format' has no attribute 'JSON'`. Because this change only removes synonyms from an already-obsolete term and does not newly obsolete the term or change replacement guidance, no annotation migration was performed.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/DESIGN_PATTERNS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,21 @@\n+# Design Pattern Notes for GO:0016430 Obsoletion Cleanup\n+\n+## Scope\n+\n+This task concerns cleanup of an already-obsolete molecular function term, `GO:0016430` obsolete tRNA (adenine-N6)-methyltransferase activity.\n+\n+## Applicable Guidance\n+\n+The term is in the catalytic activity branch and originally represented an enzyme reaction. Reaction-term guidance was consulted, but no reaction definition, RHEA mapping, EC mapping, or logical axiom was added or changed in this cleanup.\n+\n+The obsoletion pattern is the relevant pattern for the edit:\n+\n+* obsolete label is retained as `obsolete <original label>`\n+* namespace and historical obsolete definition are retained\n+* obsoletion comment and term tracker item are retained\n+* `is_obsolete: true` is retained\n+* synonyms are removed, consistent with GO obsoletion guidance that obsolete terms should not retain synonyms unless explicitly requested\n+\n+## Logical Axioms\n+\n+No `intersection_of`, `is_a`, or `relationship` tags were ad